    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Preserving Access to Manufactured Housing Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Truth in Lending Act (TILA) to specify that a retailer of manufactured housing is generally not a "mortgage originator" subject to requirements under that Act. Similarly, the bill amends the Secure and Fair Enforcement for Mortgage Licensing Act of 2008 to specify that such a retailer is generally not a "loan originator" subject to requirements under that Act.</p> <p>In addition, the bill&nbsp;increases the annual percentage rates and transaction values at which&nbsp;mortgages for certain dwellings are considered "high-cost mortgages" under TILA. </p>]]></text>
